WEBVTT

00:06.903 --> 00:09.424
3 percent rise
in domestic violence calls.

00:10.068 --> 00:12.252
So the Thanksgiving week
always brings an uptick.

00:12.573 --> 00:15.478
Families starting to gather.
In-laws in town.

00:15.503 --> 00:18.073
If the pilgrims and indians
could find a way.

00:18.098 --> 00:19.767
Maybe the first Thanksgiving
was cause they were

00:19.792 --> 00:21.468
just to worn out
to fight anymore.

00:22.011 --> 00:23.662
Where's the file
I asked you for?

00:24.058 --> 00:25.714
It's on your desk, sir.

00:27.128 --> 00:28.450
Oh.

00:29.336 --> 00:31.167
Thank you Baker.

00:36.381 --> 00:38.009
What about this Raymond thing?

00:38.657 --> 00:41.298
Corporation counsel was served
today with a lawsuit.,

00:41.323 --> 00:43.429
alleging police brutality.

00:43.793 --> 00:45.898
It claims, that two days ago,

00:45.923 --> 00:47.870
Raymond assaulted an
eight-year-old boy

00:47.895 --> 00:50.868
living on the same block
as his partner, Officer Donohue.

00:51.912 --> 00:53.103
Is the boy ok?

00:53.128 --> 00:55.846
After two hour in ER,
and multiple stitches.

00:55.871 --> 00:58.784
His father, an attorney,
named

00:59.170 --> 01:01.171
Preston Morris, says his son is

01:01.173 --> 01:03.423
"totally traumatized
by the attack,"

01:03.425 --> 01:06.509
and went straight to the
media after filing the suit.

01:06.511 --> 01:08.795
And we have no idea
why it happened.

01:08.797 --> 01:10.013
Not even from his partner.

01:10.015 --> 01:12.732
Far as anyone can tell,
Raymond just snapped.

01:12.734 --> 01:15.134
Goes without saying,
the optics are bad on this.

01:15.136 --> 01:18.304
Sterling record,
decorated twice for heroism.

01:18.306 --> 01:20.490
This is not that.

01:20.492 --> 01:24.143
He is entitled to the same
presumption of innocence

01:24.145 --> 01:27.480
afforded any other member
of my department.

01:27.482 --> 01:28.698
You'll let Legal handle it?

01:28.700 --> 01:30.667
Yes, Mrs. Reagan.

01:30.669 --> 01:32.318
Moving on.

01:39.493 --> 01:41.327
Vic was a hell of a cop.

01:41.329 --> 01:44.264
But he would be the first to say
he wasn't the best

01:44.266 --> 01:46.516
in the family.

01:46.518 --> 01:49.352
That would belong
to Colleen over there.

01:49.354 --> 01:52.021
In fact,

01:52.023 --> 01:54.274
we partnered for a while.

01:54.276 --> 01:56.843
And then she was assigned
to Vic,

01:56.845 --> 02:01.698
who said that that was
the happiest day of his life.

02:01.700 --> 02:04.617
Until, of course,
Brendan and Meara

02:04.619 --> 02:06.903
came along.

02:08.856 --> 02:11.858
May the Lord bless
Vic McGuire

02:11.860 --> 02:14.377
and keep his family
in His heart.

02:20.134 --> 02:22.502
You did good, Reagan.

02:22.504 --> 02:23.419
Thanks, Roy.

02:23.421 --> 02:25.255
Fly was open
the entire time though.

02:25.257 --> 02:27.006
Up yours, Roy.

02:29.994 --> 02:32.211
Thank you, Henry.

02:33.848 --> 02:35.982
How you doing?

02:35.984 --> 02:37.150
I'm hanging in there.

02:37.152 --> 02:38.885
This place

02:38.887 --> 02:42.155
already seems so empty
without him.

02:42.157 --> 02:44.223
You'll see him again one day.

02:45.910 --> 02:47.911
Don't be a stranger.

02:47.913 --> 02:50.280
Okay.

02:54.919 --> 02:56.252
This doesn't make sense.

02:56.254 --> 02:58.404
Brendan, I am not
imagining things.

02:58.406 --> 03:00.506
What you're saying is crazy.
I'm...

03:00.508 --> 03:01.758
Hi, kids.

03:02.626 --> 03:04.794
Hey, Mr. Reagan.

03:06.630 --> 03:08.097
Look...

03:08.099 --> 03:11.935
I've been through this
a little bit.

03:11.937 --> 03:14.470
You got to go day by day.

03:14.472 --> 03:16.022
But it will

03:16.024 --> 03:18.191
get better.

03:18.193 --> 03:19.809
Go on. Say it.

03:20.728 --> 03:22.228
Say what?

03:23.764 --> 03:26.316
Unless Dad didn't just die.

03:26.318 --> 03:28.434
What do you mean?

03:30.504 --> 03:33.706
I think Mom might've had
something to do with his death.

03:33.708 --> 03:36.275
Meara, your father died
of cancer.

03:36.277 --> 03:38.494
He's been sick
for the last eight months.

03:38.496 --> 03:39.946
No, but he was better last week.

03:39.948 --> 03:41.247
Mr. Reagan, she is just upset.

03:41.249 --> 03:42.882
And you're not?

03:42.884 --> 03:44.450
Listen to what
you're saying,

03:44.452 --> 03:46.252
Meara. It's your mother.

03:46.254 --> 03:50.289
I know how it sounds, and maybe
she didn't do anything to Dad.

03:51.675 --> 03:54.894
But I think she did.

